{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01TTrkzRBYLGiFF4hSoAJWS9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the complete picture. Let me look at the exact fix location one more time to make sure I have the right analysis:\n\nROOT CAUSE: In `libyara/parser.c:855-876`, the function `yr_parser_reduce_rule_declaration_phase_1` sets `compiler->current_rule_idx` **before** checking if a rule with the same identifier already exists. When the duplicate identifier check fails at line 876, the function returns an error, but `current_rule_idx` has already been set to an index that doesn't have an allocated rule. When `yyerror` is called during error handling, it tries to access the rule at that index via `yr_arena_get_ptr()` at lexer.c:3463, causing the assertion failure because the offset exceeds the allocated buffer size.\n\nLOCAL FIX: Move the duplicate identifier check (lines 863-877) **before** the assignment at lines 855-856.\n\nGLOBAL FIX: Add defensive bounds checking in `yyerror` (lexer.c:3463) to validate that `current_rule_idx * sizeof(YR_RULE)` doesn't exceed the allocated buffer before calling `yr_arena_get_ptr()`. This prevents similar crashes from uninitialized indices in error paths.\n\n---\n\n**ROOT CAUSE:** libyara/parser.c:855-876 — `compiler->current_rule_idx` is assigned to an unallocated rule index before validating that the rule identifier doesn't duplicate an existing rule. If a duplicate is found (ERROR_DUPLICATED_IDENTIFIER), the function returns early with `current_rule_idx` pointing to a rule that was never allocated. When `yyerror` (lexer.c:3463) tries to access this invalid index via `yr_arena_get_ptr()`, the offset exceeds the buffer's used size, failing the assertion at arena.c:391.\n\n**LOCAL FIX:** In `libyara/parser.c`, move the duplicate identifier check (lines 863-877) to execute **before** lines 855-856 that set `current_rule_idx`. This ensures the index is only set if the identifier is valid.\n\n**GLOBAL FIX:** In `libyara/lexer.c:3463` within the `yyerror` function, add a bounds check before calling `yr_arena_get_ptr()`:\n```c\nif (compiler->current_rule_idx != UINT32_MAX &&\n    compiler->current_rule_idx * sizeof(YR_RULE) <= arena->buffers[YR_RULES_TABLE].used)\n  current_rule = yr_arena_get_ptr(compiler->arena, YR_RULES_TABLE, ...);\n```\nThis defensive check prevents crashes when error handlers encounter partially-initialized parser state from early validation failures."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1147,"cache_read_input_tokens":101584,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1147},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9e882aed-4340-458c-9d0e-f5225c4c3449","uuid":"4b000b85-dd49-4bf5-9516-ff2faa5311be"}
